    <text>
        <body>
            <p>(copy)</p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                <date>July 19</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>1864</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Mr T. A. Pitt</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Hamilton Bermuda</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">There was on board the Sch.<lb/> “Responsible” <persName>cap:
                    Daville</persName>, a Box of Bibles &amp; Books<lb/> addressed to
                    <persName>Revd. M. N. Nathan</persName><lb/> care of <persName>Osorio Wright
                    &amp; Co</persName><lb/>
                <placeName>St. Thomas</placeName>,<lb/> which does not appear to have been<lb/> on
                board the Brig which took<lb/> the Responsible's cargo to <placeName>St.
                    Thomas</placeName>. If it<lb/> is still in <placeName>Bermuda</placeName>, in
                store, will you<lb/> please forward it to <placeName>St Thomas</placeName>, by<lb/>
                the steamer, or first good oppty <add>?</add><lb/> B/Lading to <persName>Revd M.
                    Nathan</persName>, care of, as<lb/> above. They were shipped by the
                    <persName>Revd.<lb/> Isaac Leeser</persName> of this city. A line<lb/> from you
                either to <persName>Mr Leeser</persName>, <placeName>1227 Walnut St<lb/>
                    Phila</placeName>, or to me, will greatly oblige</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">your obd servt</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">Alex. E. Ont<add>?</add></persName>
            </p>
        </body>
